  "prompt": "Is there an irc channel for GRE aspirants?",
  "response": "IRC (Internet Relay Chat) was once a popular platform for group discussions but has largely been supplanted by newer communication platforms. While there might be some IRC channels dedicated to GRE aspirants, it is more likely that you'll find active communities on platforms like Reddit, Discord, or specialized forums for test prep.\n\nFor example, you can find GRE discussions and resources on:\n- Reddit's r/GRE community\n- GRE-related Discord servers\n- Test prep forums such as TheGradCafe or Pagalguy\n\nThese platforms tend to have active users and a wealth of shared resources that could be more beneficial than traditional IRC channels.",
